Explanation:

We use a graph data structure to represent the prerequisites between courses. We initialize a boolean visited array to keep track of visited nodes. Then, we iterate over all courses and check if a course can be visited (has a prerequisite and is not visited) and mark it as visited. If a course can be visited, we return true, indicating that all courses can be visited. If no course can be visited after iterating through all courses, we return false.

The time complexity is O(n^2) because we iterate over all courses twice (once for each course). The space complexity is O(n) because we use a 2D boolean array to store visited courses. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only requires a small amount of energy to execute.

